# Cursor Rules for 2026 Challenge Project

## Development Environment
- Backend: FastAPI server running on `http://localhost:8000` with auto-reload enabled
- Frontend: Next.js development server running on `http://localhost:3000` with hot reload enabled
- Database: PostgreSQL running locally

## Server Management
- **DO NOT restart backend/frontend servers manually** - Both servers are already running in the background with auto-reload/hot-reload enabled
- Code changes are automatically reflected without server restart
- Backend uses `--reload` flag, Frontend uses development mode with hot module replacement

## Project Structure
- Backend: `/backend` directory (FastAPI)
- Frontend: `/frontend` directory (Next.js + TypeScript)
- Database: PostgreSQL with SQLAlchemy ORM
- Admin interface: `/frontend/app/admin` routes

## Development Workflow
- Make code changes directly - servers will auto-reload
- Test API endpoints via browser or API client
- Frontend components auto-refresh on changes
- Database migrations handled automatically via SQLAlchemy

## Common Operations
- Backend API testing: Use TestClient or direct HTTP requests
- Frontend testing: Use browser development tools
- Database operations: Use SQLAlchemy ORM methods
- Admin interface: Access via `/admin` routes

## Performance Notes
- Development servers are optimized for fast reloads
- No need to stop/start servers between changes
- Hot reload provides instant feedback for UI changes
